Begar, dat be very merry Gentilman;

                     Sir Humphrey finds a Country Peasant leaning upon his Staff; he strikes it away, and he falls backward. Another Peasant knocks Sir Hum. down: he rises, and Draws. Several of the Mobile joyn with the Peasant: the Gentlemen Draw, and Rescue him. The Ladies shriek, and run away.

he have de great deal of Wit, assurement ouy. Teste bleau, de Insolence of Peasant English!

